</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,544,1945,1969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[463,544,1945,1969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. 1. 
<taxonomicName box="[584,736,1945,1969]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laceyi">
<emphasis box="[584,736,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Quercus laceyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with mature galls. 2. Mature galls with an emergence hole. 3. Cross section of gall showing adult and empty chambers. 4. Live anterodorsal habitus. 5. Lateral habitus of holotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876435" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6876435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876435/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" startId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[179,1408,181,1920]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1943,2004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,328,1943,1967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">FIGURES 6–12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Sasan &amp; O’Kennon &amp; Kranz, 2022" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Sasan &amp; O’Kennon &amp; Kranz" authorityYear="2022" box="[335,468,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laceyi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[335,468,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Druon laceyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
