</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,762,788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Distribution.</emphasis>
Currently known only from Texas. It is possible that this species also occurs in Oklahoma and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[254,342,799,825]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, where the host plant is known. Further research is necessary to establish the distribution of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,819,871,897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,897]" box="[199,819,871,897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,871,897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after its host plant, 
<taxonomicName box="[644,812,871,897]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laceyi">
<emphasis box="[644,812,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Quercus laceyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
